        <abstract>
            <p>To Lyell’s chagrin, CD has come round again to A. C. Ramsay’s glacial theory.</p>
            <p>On primrose and cowslip, CD maintains they are good species, notwithstanding Scott’s work.</p>
            <p>CD defines species by power of remaining constant for a good long time and showing appreciable amount of difference from close species.</p>
        </abstract>
